Trend Analysis¶

In [7]:
# Grouping by 'release_year' and counting the number of movies released each year
yearly_counts = netflix['release_year'].value_counts().sort_index()
In [8]:
# Plotting the trend of movie releases over the years
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
yearly_counts.plot(kind='line')
plt.title('Number of Movies Released Each Year')
plt.xlabel('Release Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Movies')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show
Out[8]:
<function matplotlib.pyplot.show(close=None, block=None)>

# Counting the number of movies by type
type_counts = netflix['type'].value_counts()
In [14]:
# Plotting the distribution of movie types
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
type_counts.plot(kind='bar')
plt.title('Distribution of Movie Types')
plt.xlabel('Type')
plt.ylabel('Number of Movies')
plt.xticks(rotation=0)
plt.show()

Duration Analysis¶

In [23]:
# Plotting the distribution of movie durations
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.hist(netflix['duration'], bins=30, edgecolor='black')
plt.title('Distribution of Movie Durations')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.xlabel('Duration (minutes)')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()
